title: Elle King Admits she Was ‘High AF’ On Pot Muffins at the Grammys
text:
PHOTOS: See the 5 Biggest Beauty Trends From the Grammys 2017 Red Carpet 
King wore a floral Teuta Matoshi dress and matching Lirika Matoshi flower headband, but admitted her clothing choice may have been a mistake. A post shared by Elle King (@elleking) on Feb 13, 2017 at 7:56pm PST 
“Sometimes when you’re accidentally high af from pot muffins and you don’t realize you’re A F—KING SNAPCHAT FILTER until after the Grammys and people tell you,” she wrote. A post shared by Elle King (@elleking) on Feb 13, 2017 at 8:21pm PST 
King, who is the daughter of actor Rob Schneider , also took the opportunity to post a video of herself being interviewed while high, and apologized to her mom for her behavior. Elle King at the 2017 Grammys Getty 
The 27-year-old was nominated for a Grammy in the Best Country Dup/Group Performance category for her song “Different for Girls” with Dierks Bentley .
